hi @miguelgrinberg ,

2 Weeks of testing and observation I managed to stabilize the servers with the following fix:

```python
    def _emit_internal(self, sid, event, data, namespace=None, id=None):
        """Send a message to a client."""
        if six.PY2 and not self.binary:
            binary = False  # pragma: nocover
        else:
            binary = None
        # tuples are expanded to multiple arguments, everything else is sent
        # as a single argument
        if isinstance(data, tuple):
            data = list(data)
        else:
            data = [data]

        try:
            self._send_packet(sid, packet.Packet(packet.EVENT, namespace=namespace,
                                                 data=[event] + data, id=id,
                                                 binary=binary))
        except:
            self.logger.error('error in _emit_internal %s', sid)
            try:
                self._trigger_event('disconnect', namespace, sid)
                self.manager.disconnect(sid, namespace=namespace)
            except:
                self.logger.error('error in _emit_internal cleanup %s', sid)
                pass
```

It just happens that there were two different cases of happening.   One case, was the send_packet not able to send due to sid is not available, and after doing the cleanup of the event handler some response are successful but others were throwing errors on the cleanup process.  I just added a try catch on the cleanup process to allow.

@ShipraShalini 

Wow, that's a lot of code. This should be simpler. :) 

So, you have a MapField of EmbeddedDocuments like this:

```
class Song(EmbeddedDocument):
    title = fields.StringField()
    context = fields.FileField()

class Album(EmbeddedDocument):
    date = fields.DateTimeField()
    songs = fields.EmbeddedDocumentListField(Song)

class RockBand(Document):
    albums = fields.MapField(fields.EmbeddedDocumentField(Album))
```


 and your `validated_data` looks like this:

```
{
    "Queen": {
        "Night in the Opera": {
            "date": "11-21-1975"
            "songs": [
                {
                    "title": "Bohemian Rhapsody",
                    "content": <urlencoded content>
                }
            ] 
        }
    }
}
```

Is your `field` a `DocumentSerializer` field or a `Document` field? It should be `Document` field, right?

Now, in my example `key=Night in the Opera`, `k="date", "songs" etc.`, so `validated_data[key][k]` is `"11-21-1975"` or `[{"title": "Bohemian Rhapsody", "content": <urlencoded content>}]`. The latter is not a valid `EmbeddedDocumentListField` - it's just a python list that needs to be converted to EmbeddedDocumentListField.

Same is true for any EmbeddedDocument you have - `validated_data[key][k]` is a dict, not EmbeddedDocument.

Also, I don't know, what is `update_set()` function, you're using.

Thanks, this is a confirmed bug.  I believe this regressed when we switched over to generating a swagger file internally.  I think the `parameters` field we generate isn't at the right level of nesting.  It also appears that API Gateway ignores fields it doesn't understand:

**What we generate**
```json
          "paths": {
            "/hello/{name}": {
              "get": {
                "responses": {
                  "200": {
                    "description": "200 response",
                    "schema": {
                      "$ref": "#/definitions/Empty"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "x-amazon-apigateway-integration": {
                  "contentHandling": "CONVERT_TO_TEXT",
                  "responses": {
                    "default": {
                      "statusCode": "200"
                    }
                  },
                  "parameters": [
                    {
                      "required": true,
                      "type": "string",
                      "name": "name",
                      "in": "path"
                    }
                  ],
```

**What we actually need to generate**
```
    "/hello/{name}": {
      "get": {
        "produces": [
          "application/json"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "name",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "200 response",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/Empty"
            }
          }
        },
        "x-amazon-apigateway-integration": {
          "responses": {
            "default": {
              "statusCode": "200"
            }
          },
```

Note the `parameters` should be moved up a level.

Thanks for reporting we'll get this fixed.

Fish,

There is really no way to differentiate, between a jump or return when PC is loaded.

However, libvex already has some code where load/mov pc variants are assumed to be Ijk_Ret.

Below are examples from https://github.com/angr/vex/tree/master/priv/guest_arm_toIR.c:

```
....
   /* According to the Cortex A8 TRM Sec. 5.2.1, LDM(1) with r13 as the base
       register and PC in the register list is a return for purposes of branch
       prediction.
      The ARM ARM Sec. C9.10.1 further specifies that writeback must be enabled
       to be counted in event 0x0E (Procedure return).*/
   if (rN == 13 && bL == 1 && bINC && !bBEFORE && bW == 1) {
      jk = Ijk_Ret;
}

....


            /* According to the Cortex A8 TRM Sec. 5.2.1, MOV PC, r14 is a
                return for purposes of branch prediction. */
            if (!isMVN && INSN(11,0) == 14) {
              jk = Ijk_Ret;
}
....

          /* According to the Cortex A8 TRM Sec. 5.2.1, LDR(1) with r13 as the
               base register and PC as the destination register is a return for
               purposes of branch prediction.
              The ARM ARM Sec. C9.10.1 further specifies that it must use a
               post-increment by immediate addressing mode to be counted in
               event 0x0E (Procedure return).*/
           if (rN == 13 && summary == (3 | 16) && bB == 0) {
              jk = Ijk_Ret;
}

....
```
Case for **LDR PC, [SP],#4** is in no way different from the ones mentioned above. libvex developers had even left comment  about that: 

```
....
   /* ---------------- LD/ST reg+/-#imm8 ---------------- */
   /* Loads and stores of the form:
         op  Rt, [Rn, #-imm8]      or
         op  Rt, [Rn], #+/-imm8    or
         op  Rt, [Rn, #+/-imm8]!  
      where op is one of
         ldrb ldrh ldr  ldrsb ldrsh
         strb strh str
   */
....  
            if (loadsPC) {
               /* Presumably this is an interworking branch. */
               vassert(rN != 15); // assured by validity check above
               vassert(rT == 15);
               vassert(condT == IRTemp_INVALID); /* due to check above */
               llPutIReg(15, mkexpr(newRt));
               dres.jk_StopHere = Ijk_Boring;  /* or _Ret ? */
               dres.whatNext    = Dis_StopHere;
}
....
```

They definitely had doubts whether it is Ijk_Boring or Ijk_Ret, but probably didn't have enough time or resources to thoroughly check that.

I'll prepare pull request for https://github.com/angr/vex and show you guys.

@iamyoungjo According to your log, the reason why it is still failing is that the default linking args `-lcublas` could only search in library files from`/usr/lib` `/usr/local/lib`, while the default path for cuda is `/usr/local/cuda/lib`.

A work around should be expending search path using `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` under osx, like this:
`export CUDA_HOME="/usr/local/cuda"`
 `export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH="/usr/local/cuda/lib"`
To point our, for OSX >10.11, you need to turning off Rootless System Integrity Protection to honor `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` variable. Follow this [link](http://osxdaily.com/2015/10/05/disable-rootless-system-integrity-protection-mac-os-x/)

